# HLV Slide Design

Rules and patterns for creating HLV presentation slides. Built from Apple design research and refined through production.

---

## Core Principle

**One idea per slide. Let it breathe.**

More slides with less content beats fewer slides crammed full. The empty space is the design.

---

## Slide Spacing

### Container Padding
```
Desktop (16:9):
  Top/Bottom: 80px
  Left/Right: 120px
```

### Content Density Rule
**Aim for 30-40% content, 60-70% space.**

If a slide feels cramped, split it. Don't shrink the content.

---

## Typography Scale for Slides

| Element | Size | Weight | Line Height |
|---------|------|--------|-------------|
| Display (hero titles) | 72px | 700 | 1.0 |
| Headline | 48px | 700 | 1.15 |
| Title | 32px | 600 | 1.2 |
| Subhead | 24px | 600 | 1.25 |
| Body | 18-21px | 400 | 1.5 |
| Caption/Eyebrow | 12px | 600 | 1.4 |

### Eyebrow Pattern
```
FOUNDATION CHAPTER          ← 12px, 600 weight, emerald, letter-spacing 0.15-0.2em
                            ← 24-32px gap
Problem Reframing           ← Display headline
```

