## Critical Spacing Rules

### Gap vs Line Height (LEARNED)

**Problem:** Stacked text blocks that are part of the same thought looked disconnected.

**Rule:** Use explicit gap values, not line-height, to control spacing between text blocks.

| Relationship | Gap |
|--------------|-----|
| Same thought (e.g., "Same problem." / "Different solutions.") | 0-8px |
| Related items in a list | 16px |
| Distinct sections | 40-56px |
| Eyebrow to headline | 24-32px |
| Headline to body | 32-48px |

**Wrong:**
```jsx
<h2 style={{ marginTop: 8 }}>Same problem.</h2>
<h2 style={{ marginTop: 8 }}>Different solution spaces.</h2>
```

**Right:**
```jsx
<h2>
  <span style={{ display: 'block' }}>Same problem.</span>
  <span style={{ display: 'block' }}>Different solution spaces.</span>
</h2>
```

Or use controlled gap:
```jsx
<div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: 4 }}>
```

---

### Number + Text Alignment (LEARNED)

**Problem:** Large decorative numbers (01, 02...) misalign with adjacent text.

**Rule:** Align numbers to `flex-start`, not baseline. Add small `marginTop` for optical alignment.

**Pattern:**
```jsx
<div style={{ 
  display: 'flex', 
  alignItems: 'flex-start',  // NOT baseline
  gap: 24,
}}>
  <span style={{ 
    fontSize: 48, 
    fontWeight: 700, 
    opacity: 0.2,
    lineHeight: 1,
    width: 72,           // Fixed width
    flexShrink: 0,
    marginTop: 2,        // Optical adjustment
  }}>
    01
  </span>
  <div>
    <p style={{ fontSize: 24, fontWeight: 600 }}>Title</p>
    <p style={{ fontSize: 16, color: gray }}>Description</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

